The '''two-banded warbler''' ('''''Myiothlypis bivittata''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Parulidae]]. It is found in [[Argentina]], [[Bolivia]], [[Brazil]], [[Guyana]], [[Peru]], and [[Venezuela]].  Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s and heavily degraded former forest.

